The UN is considering greater protection for various species, including pink coral and cedar trees, due to threats like overexploitation.
The EU is pushing for permits on trade in European eels and spiny dogfish.
Coral reefs face extinction risks from climate change, impacting biodiversity.
The global trade in coral is being regulated to prevent further depletion.
Efforts are underway to restore damaged coral reefs, with a focus on sustainable conservation practices.
Tourism partnerships are aiding in reef conservation, highlighting the importance of collaboration in protecting marine ecosystems.
